Mexico’s Senate Ratifies Marisela Morales as Attorney General

-- B y   A d r i a n a   L o p e z   C a r a v e o
-- 
2011-04-07T19:16:56Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-07/mexico-s-senate-ratifies-marisela-morales-as-attorney-general.html
Mexico ’s Senate ratified Marisela
Morales as the country’s new attorney general, after President
Felipe Calderon nominated her to replace Arturo Chavez Chavez,
who resigned last week.  Lawmakers ratified Morales with 84 votes in favor and 15
against. Morales was head of the organized crime unit of the
federal attorney general’s office until March 31. She is a
lawyer who graduated from the Mexico’s Autonomous National
University.  On March 8 Morales received from U.S. First Lady Michelle Obama and Secretary of State  Hillary Clinton  the 2010
International Women of Courage Award, or IWOC, due to her
courage in fighting drug cartels in Mexico, according to the
attorney general’s office  website .  To contact the reporters on this story:
